      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "failure_policy_drift"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "unwrapped_transition_errors",
      "summary": "Broadcast transition application returns implementation errors without boundary context.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/broadcast/transitions.go",
        "goseg/broadcast/loop.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`ApplyBroadcastTransition` returns `transition.Apply` errors directly (`return err`) with no transition type or operation context.",
        "Adjacent broadcast code (`buildBroadcastTickState`) wraps errors with contextual operation labels (e.g., `\"unable to build pier info: %w\"`), demonstrating inconsistent boundary behavior within the same subsystem."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Wrap transition application failures with transition identity and operation context, e.g. `fmt.Errorf(\"apply broadcast transition %T: %w\", transition, err)`.",
